        "intro_content": "<p>The <strong>gyuto knife</strong> is Japan's answer to the Western chef knife. Thinner, lighter, and ground to a sharper 15-degree angle, the gyuto delivers precision cuts that heavier European blades struggle to match. Australian home cooks increasingly choose gyuto knives for everyday prep because they slice with less effort and hold their edge longer. XinZuo gyuto knives feature 67-layer Damascus steel with a 10Cr15CoMoV core, forged in Yangjiang to hardness levels that German steel cannot reach. If you want one <strong>kitchen knife</strong> that handles everything from vegetables to proteins, the gyuto is the professional's choice. For a shorter alternative, consider the santoku.</p>",
